---
By: Walter Russell
Locus:
  Page: 127
  Verse: 9
Tags:
  - Enlightenment
---
Think of it how simple it is to know that the joy of achievement recharges
you with a balancing energy for the next achievement. If you have no joy or
happiness in your work, finding it to be a drudgery instead, you will find
fatigue from the constant devitalizing draining of energy.
